dismissalText.commentary: Imran Nazir c & b Pollock 22 (22b 2x4 1x6 30m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Pollock gets his man! Nazir tries to play the same hoick that earlier resulted in a six over midwicket, this time he gets the bottom half of the bat on it and sends the ball soaring high high into the air, Pollock calls for it and waits for what seems like an eternity before taking a steepling catch

headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Hafeez headshot

dismissalComment.html: and caught! Pollock strikes in trademark fashion, he teased Hafeez with the first five balls by moving them away from a good length, this time he bowls it a little fuller, drawing Hafeez forward and inducing the drive, the movement off the pitch drew the edge and Boucher takes a simple catch

headshotImage.caption: Younis Khan headshot
headshotImage.longCaption: Younis Khan headshot

dismissalComment.html: bowled him! Pollock does what he has been doing almost every ball, bowls it on a superb length and line outside off stump, Younis plays away from his body and tries to drive, he gets a thick inside edge and the ball uproots the off stump

headshotImage.caption: Mohammad Yousuf player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Yousuf player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Pollock gets his fourth! He pitches that just outside off stump and angles it into Yousuf who fell over a little as he tried to flick, the ball hit him in front of middle stump, Rudi Koertzen answers the confident appeal with the slow raise of his index finger

headshotImage.caption: Inzamam-ul-Haq player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Inzamam-ul-Haq player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Pollock has five out of five! He bowls that just outside off stump and the ball rears sharly off a good length, Inzamam tries to cut but the ball is far too close to the body and the bounce cramps him for room, he edges it to Kallis who takes a sharp catch above his head at second slip

headshotImage.longCaption: Naved-ul-Hasan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Kallis bangs the bouncer in, Rana Naved tries to hook but doesn't get into proper position, the ball takes the edge and Boucher roars an appeal after taking the catch, Kallis is confident but Rana Naved isn't happy with the decision

dismissalComment.html: Kallis bangs it in short and down leg side, Rao Iftikhar moves across his stumps and tries to play it down to fine leg, he gets a bit of glove on it and Boucher accepts the catch with glee

commentTextItems.html: victory for South Africa, de Villiers nudges it late and nudges it fine and times it well enough for the ball to scurry to the third man fence

commentPostTextItems.html: South Africa take the series 3-1 with this emphatic nine-wicket victory. Shaun Pollock set it up for them by decimating Pakistan's top-order with a ten-over spell that yeilded 5 for 23. They were dismissed for 153 and it was never going to be enough even after Graeme Smith was dismissed of fthe first ball of the chase.

de Villiers and Kallis struck aggressive fifties and took South Africa home with 22.4 overs to spare. You would have hoped that Pakistan would fight hard and give us a tight contest to enjoy but once again South Africa have swamped them and finished off another one-sided match.
Shaun Pollock is the Man of the Match, no surprises there. His spell knocked Pakistan out of the contest. He is also the Man of the Series, his third such award of the summer.

South Africa will head to the Caribbean with supreme confidence and they certainly are among the favourites to win the World Cup. Pakistan, on the other hand, have a fantastic team on paper but they have been woefully flat on the field barring the fabulous Asif.
That's it from us at Cricinfo, congratulations to South Africa. This is George Binoy saying goodnight.

commentTextItems.html: Kallis steers it behind point for one more run
dabbed in front of point for a single, that takes South Africa to 151, just three runs away from taking the series

dismissalText.commentary: Graeme Smith c †Kamran Akmal b Mohammad Asif 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Asif strikes with his first legitimate ball! And what a snorter of a ball, it burst off a good length outside off stump and angled away from Smith, he poked at it and nicked it to Akmal, that one cut viciously off the pitch, it was unplayable

stories.title: Pollock sets up crushing win
stories.subTitle: South Africa v Pakistan, 5th ODI, Johannesburg
stories.summary: Shaun Pollock sashayed a path through Pakistan's top order with a fifth five-wicket haul, as the tourists limped to a painfully inadequate 153 all out in the final ODI at the Wanderers

stories.title: Pakistan cool their heels as equipment goes missing
stories.subTitle: South Africa v Pakistan, 5th ODI, Johannesburg
stories.summary: Pakistan's preparations for the final ODI against South Africa at Johannesburg have been hampered by the disappearance of key analytical equipment en route from Cape Town.

stories.title: Rao Iftikhar likely to play final ODI
stories.subTitle: South Africa v Pakistan, 5th ODI, Johannesburg
stories.summary: Rao Iftikhar Anjum, one of several back-up seamers called to South Africa during Pakistan's troubled tour, looks set to get the call-up into the starting XI for the final one-day international at the Wanderers on Wednesday
